{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the diversity of experiences that STEM teachers bring, as noted by El Nagdi et al. (2018), can both be an asset and a challenge in integrating new STEM teaching concepts.",
    "The rich diversity of teachers' backgrounds can enhance professional development by allowing them to connect new STEM teaching methods to their prior knowledge and experience.",
    "However, challenges may arise when new learning contradicts established teaching methods or beliefs (Avraamidou, 2019).",
    "The motivation for adult learners, particularly STEM teachers, often stems from immediate professional needs and challenges (Jiang et al. 2021).",
    "Thus, the analysis focuses on how well the TPD programs align with teachers' current goals and professional requirements, integrating modern teaching methods and technologies (Scaradozzi et al. 2019)."
  ]
}